hollywood
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a feigned injury; esp. in to do/pull/throw a hollywood, to feign or exaggerate the seriousness of an injury during a game
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: (sporting) (informal) 1984 16 F E8 Pakuranga Coll. 31 HOLLYWOOD -->1984 14 F E125Wgton Girls C. 35C HOLLYWOOD: FAKING SOMETHING
